# Mission Control — API config. Copy to api/.env and fill in. NEVER commit real values.
# All keys are optional; absent ones simply leave that feature off (non-invasive by default).

# --- Event store ---
# Where the local SQLite event store lives (default: ~/.mission-control/events.db).
# MC_DB_PATH=/Users/you/.mission-control/events.db

# --- Jump-to-agent (v1.5) ---
# Set to 1 to let POST /api/jump actually launch the resume command locally (default: off;
# the command is always returned for copy/paste regardless).
# MC_ENABLE_JUMP=1

# --- Claude remaining-window quota (v2) ---
# Set to 1 to show Claude's real remaining quota (5h + weekly gauges, like the Claude usage page)
# instead of only consumed tokens. This reads your Claude OAuth token at runtime (macOS Keychain,
# or ~/.claude/.credentials.json on Linux) for a single read-only GET /api/oauth/usage — the token
# is held in memory only, never persisted/logged/sent to the browser. Off by default (opt-in).
# MC_ENABLE_CLAUDE_QUOTA=1

# --- Slack collector (v2) ---
# A Slack USER token (xoxp-…) so Mission Control can read YOUR DMs + mentions ("buried items").
# Read-only; held in memory only for each request; never persisted, logged, or sent to the browser.
# When unset, the Slack collector stays off. How to get one: see api/SLACK_SETUP.md.
# SLACK_TOKEN=xoxp-your-user-token-here
